{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0164yvVnuaC9pJXqExk9Wokw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue. The StatefulSet is only creating pod-0, and it's not creating pod-1 and pod-2. This is because the StatefulSet by default uses `OrderedReady` pod management policy, which means it waits for pod-0 to be Ready before creating pod-1. But pod-0 can't become Ready because it needs to join a cluster with at least 2 other nodes (or be initialized with `cockroach init`).\n\nThis is a classic chicken-and-egg problem with CockroachDB StatefulSets. The solution is to use `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` so all pods start simultaneously, and then run `cockroach init` once they're all up.\nI need to delete the StatefulSet and recreate it with `Parallel` pod management policy, which will let all three pods start at once. Once they're all Running, I can initialize the cluster with `cockroach init`.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1657,"cache_read_input_tokens":32603,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1657},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fbdbfb21-4e20-4e4a-ba5a-231291bd1a4b","uuid":"04172405-44b6-43d6-80cd-57de1c3e00e8","request_id":"req_011CcMPeBpWBNzJBmEqEEtZE"}
